I just ran: dnf update --enablepro=fedora --enablerepo=updates --enablerepo=updates-testing xfwm4-4.12.4-1.fc25
No more crashes. For informational purposes attached is a verbose xfce log as well as some logs from /var/log/messages after the dnf update:

So, it's working normally with the xfwm4 from updates-testing?
Yes just that emacs font is super small.

ok, that one should be headed to stable updates now. :)
Thanks for the report...
Any clue on the emacs font problem?

Not sure off hand, but you should be able to increase the font size?
If not, there's also Xfce settings font settings that you could change the dpi value on and make everything bigger.
